---
import MarketingLayout from '@/layouts/MarketingLayout.astro';
---

<MarketingLayout
	title="Terms of Service"
	description="LastRite's terms of service — the agreement governing use of our platform"
>
	<main class="legal-page">
		<div class="legal-content">
	<h2>Agreement to Terms</h2>
	<p>
		By accessing and using LastRite's website and services, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you
		do not agree to abide by the above, please do not use this service.
	</p>

	<h2>Use License</h2>
	<p>
		LastRite grants you a limited, non-exclusive, revocable license to access and use our website and services for
		personal, non-commercial purposes. You agree not to:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Reproduce, distribute, or transmit content without written permission</li>
		<li>Modify, adapt, or create derivative works from our services</li>
		<li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or attempt to discover source code</li>
		<li>Remove or alter any proprietary notices or labels</li>
		<li>Use the service for commercial purposes or competitive advantage</li>
		<li>Engage in automated access or scraping of our site</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>User Responsibilities</h2>
	<h3>Account Creation</h3>
	<p>
		If you create an account with LastRite, you are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your login
		credentials and for all activities that occur under your account. You agree to:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Provide accurate and complete information</li>
		<li>Keep your password secure and not share it with others</li>
		<li>Immediately notify us of any unauthorized access</li>
		<li>Accept responsibility for all activities under your account</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Content Guidelines</h3>
	<p>
		When creating or sharing content on LastRite, you agree that your content:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Will not contain defamatory, abusive, or threatening language</li>
		<li>Will not infringe on third-party intellectual property rights</li>
		<li>Will not be spam, harassment, or malicious</li>
		<li>Will not contain personal information shared without consent</li>
		<li>Will respect the dignity and memory of the deceased</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Intellectual Property Rights</h2>
	<p>
		All content on the LastRite website, including text, graphics, logos, images, and software, is the property of
		LastRite or its content suppliers and is protected by international copyright laws. You may not reproduce,
		distribute, or transmit any content without our prior written consent.
	</p>

	<h3>User-Generated Content</h3>
	<p>
		When you submit content to LastRite (such as obituaries, memories, or comments), you retain ownership of your
		content. However, you grant LastRite a worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free license to use, reproduce, modify,
		publish, and display your content in connection with providing our services.
	</p>

	<h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
	<p>
		TO THE FULLEST EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, LASTRITE SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL,
		CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, INCLUDING LOSS OF PROFITS, DATA, OR USE, EVEN IF ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY
		OF SUCH DAMAGES.
	</p>
	<p>
		Our services are provided "as is" and "as available." LastRite makes no warranties, express or implied,
		regarding the accuracy, reliability, or completeness of our services.
	</p>

	<h2>Indemnification</h2>
	<p>
		You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless LastRite and its officers, directors, employees, and agents
		from any claims, damages, losses, or expenses (including legal fees) arising from:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Your use of our services</li>
		<li>Your violation of these Terms of Service</li>
		<li>Your violation of any law or third-party rights</li>
		<li>Content you submit or share on our platform</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Termination</h2>
	<p>
		LastRite reserves the right to terminate or suspend your account and access to our services at any time, with or
		without cause, and without notice. Grounds for termination include:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Violation of these Terms of Service</li>
		<li>Abusive, threatening, or harassing behavior</li>
		<li>Posting of illegal or prohibited content</li>
		<li>Unauthorized access attempts</li>
		<li>Any conduct harmful to other users or LastRite</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Payment Terms</h2>
	<p>
		If you purchase any paid services through LastRite, you agree to pay the fees specified at the time of purchase.
		Unless otherwise stated, all fees are:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Billed at the frequency you select</li>
		<li>Non-refundable except where required by law</li>
		<li>Automatically renewed at the end of each billing period unless cancelled</li>
	</ul>
	<p>You can cancel your subscription at any time through your account settings.</p>

	<h2>Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
	<p>
		LastRite provides its services on an "as is" and "as available" basis. We make no representations or warranties
		of any kind, express or implied, regarding:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>The operation of our website or services</li>
		<li>The accuracy or reliability of information provided</li>
		<li>Freedom from errors, viruses, or harmful components</li>
		<li>Uninterrupted availability of our services</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Dispute Resolution</h2>
	<h3>Informal Resolution</h3>
	<p>
		If you have a dispute with LastRite, we encourage you to contact us first to attempt to resolve the matter
		informally. Please contact us at support@lastrite.com with a detailed description of your concern.
	</p>

	<h3>Binding Arbitration</h3>
	<p>
		Any disputes not resolved informally shall be resolved by binding arbitration in accordance with applicable law.
		Both parties waive the right to trial by jury and the right to participate in a class action.
	</p>

	<h2>Governing Law</h2>
	<p>
		These Terms of Service shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of [Your Jurisdiction],
		without regard to its conflict of law principles.
	</p>

	<h2>Entire Agreement</h2>
	<p>
		These Terms of Service, along with our Privacy Policy and any other policies posted on our website, constitute
		the entire agreement between you and LastRite regarding your use of our services and supersede all prior or
		contemporaneous agreements.
	</p>

	<h2>Modifications to Terms</h2>
	<p>
		LastRite reserves the right to modify these Terms of Service at any time. Changes will be effective immediately
		upon posting to our website. Your continued use of our services following any modifications constitutes your
		acceptance of the updated terms.
	</p>

	<h2>Severability</h2>
	<p>
		If any provision of these Terms of Service is found to be invalid or unenforceable, the remaining provisions
		shall continue in full force and effect.
	</p>

	<h2>Contact Information</h2>
	<p>For questions or concerns regarding these Terms of Service, please contact us at:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Email: legal@lastrite.com</li>
		<li>Mailing Address: [Your Company Address]</li>
		<li>Phone: [Your Phone Number]</li>
	</ul>

	<hr />
	<p><small>Last Updated: April 23, 2026</small></p>
		</div>
	</main>

	<style>
		main {
			width: calc(100% - 2rem);
			max-width: 900px;
			margin: 0 auto;
			padding: 4rem 1rem;
		}
		.legal-content {
			color: var(--color-on-surface);
			line-height: 1.6;
		}
		.legal-content h2 {
			margin-top: 2rem;
			margin-bottom: 1rem;
			font-family: var(--font-display);
			font-size: 1.5rem;
		}
		.legal-content h3 {
			margin-top: 1.5rem;
			margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
			font-family: var(--font-display);
			font-size: 1.125rem;
		}
		.legal-content p,
		.legal-content li {
			margin-bottom: 1rem;
			font-family: var(--font-body);
		}
		.legal-content ul {
			margin-left: 2rem;
			margin-bottom: 1rem;
		}
		.legal-content hr {
			margin: 2rem 0;
			border: none;
			border-top: 1px solid var(--color-outline);
		}
	</style>
</MarketingLayout>
